ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Site
Notes: Study Site

ElementDescription: Clinical status risk level
Notes: 1 = Low (Asymptomatic recovery), 2 = High (Symptomatic recovery, Recovering, Prodromal, Continued Symptomatic)

ElementDescription: Pregnancy risk level
Notes: 0 = Low (Not pregnant), 1 = High (Pregnant)

ElementDescription: Treatment arm
Final enrollment status
Notes: 1 = Completed study, 2 = Voluntarily withdrew, 3 =  Lost to follow up

ElementDescription: Weeks to relapse
Notes: Total number of weeks to mood episode; - 1 = Baseline only, -2 = Never relapsed final assessment prior to week 48, -3 = Never relapsed

ElementDescription: Clinical status code at time of relapse
Notes: '-2 = Never relapsed final assessment prior to week 48 , -1 = Baseline assessment only, 0 = Never Relapsed, 5 = Hypomania, 6 = Mania, 7 = Depression, 8 = Mixed

ElementDescription: Percent time symptomatic
Notes: Percent of weeks assessed with psychiatric status rating > 1.5, -1 = Baseline only

ElementDescription: Cumulative weeks symptomatic
Notes: Total number of weeks with psychiatric status rating > 1.5, -1 = Baseline only

ElementDescription: Cumulative weeks in study
Notes: Total number of weeks assessed using longitudinal interval evaluation

ElementDescription: Number of assessments completed
Notes: Number of planned study assessments completed after baseline assessment at enrollment

ElementDescription: Final assessment completed
Notes: Assessment month label (Month 0, 2, 4, 6, 8, 10, or 12)
